lass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1657094583441" data-id="1657094583441"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1657030716163" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1657030716163"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><strong>Using Nike Blazers for weightlifting is good because they allow for foot control as you can grip your feet and create a stable lifting platform. But the flat heel can cause some ankle mobility issues, and the lack of cushioning restricts the variety of exercises you can perform with the shoe.</strong></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1656944560008" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1656944560008" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs Nike Blazers" data-exc="Nike Blazers"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/b9ebe692-a7b5-4aec-8b4b-76a4c3850cac/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Nike-Blazers.jpg" alt="10mm Leather Weight Lifting Belt on a Weightlifter" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1280" height="853" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1280" natural-height="853"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1655318077242" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1655318077242"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Reasons to Wear Nike Blazers for Weightlifting</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658535828348" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1658535828348"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">They Have Flat Soles</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550462361" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550462361" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When lifting weights, you want to have a flat, stable surface to reduce the risk of injury and to maximize your lifting potential. Your shoes play as much of a role in this as the gym surface itself. That’s why running shoes don’t make the <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-olympic-lifting-shoes" class="">best lifting shoes</a> because their soles have too much give and can cause instability as you lift.</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550523112" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550523112" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>But, the Nike Blazers give you a nice flat surface because they have flat soles. You can almost get the sense that you’re lifting barefoot, as you can feel each individual part of your foot on the ground. This is great for distributing the weight evenly throughout your foot.</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550521842" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550521842" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>This also helps with gripping the floor better, and being able to activate your muscles from your feet up, providing you a more stable and powerful lift.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658543988733" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1658543988733"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">They Have Less Cushioning</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550492889" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550492889"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The more cushioning the shoe has, the harder it is to connect your foot to the ground. Exercises such as deadlifts and squats require you to be able to drive your heel into the ground, so you can generate enough power. While lifts like single leg RDLs require you to grip the floor with your feet to create balance and stability as you perform the exercise. With Nike Blazers, the lack of cushioning allows you to achieve both things. As the less cushion allows you to make use of your feet better and you can properly drive through your heels.</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550611173" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550611173"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Additionally, using Nike Blazers for gym is good because the lack of cushioning helps with the mind-muscle connection with your feet, which will in turn result in stronger feet, as you get a better sense of how to plant your foot, and how to use it during a lift.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658543989511" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1658543989511"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">They Provide Ankle Stability</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550499658" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550499658"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Ankle stability is an important factor when lifting, especially if you’re going heavy. Any weak link in your body is likely to get exposed during a lift, which can cause injuries. Ankles are a complicated joint that needs protection and stability, which the Nike Blazers provide with their <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-high-top-workout-shoes" class="">high tops</a> because they are narrow and have a snug fit.</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550631633" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550631633"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Many people also struggle to get the proper ankle mobility, as it’s a joint that requires regular stretching and mobility drills. So, by having a tool that helps stabilize the ankle for you, you’re likely to create better stability and balance, which will help reduce the risk of injury as it curves the overall range of motion of the lift.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658548305824" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1658548305824"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Why Nike Blazers May Not Be Best for Gym</h2></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1662730796562" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1662730796562" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BMrfRUuwmnA" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550677203" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1658550677203"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">They Provide Limited Workout Options</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550684040" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550684040"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Although Nike Blazers are suitable for lifting, they aren’t the best shoe for cardio because of their flat soles. So, if you prefer to do <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-shoes-for-hiit-workouts" class="">high-intensity interval training</a> workouts, where you incorporate cardio in between your lifts, you might end up damaging your foot because of the lack of cushioning.</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658550704521" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658550704521"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Or, if you enjoy doing more explosive workouts that include jumping and landing heavily on your foot, the Nike Blazers might not fit your lifting needs, as the lack of cushion will result in you landing too heavily on your foot and possibly hurting it.</p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1673379123157" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1673379123157" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><!-- Begin Mailchimp Signup Form --><style>.evg-mail-form h3 {margin-top: 0;}.evg-mail-form {margin: 50px 0;border-radius: 7px;border: 1px solid #bbbbbb;padding: 22px;padding-right: 50px;position: relative;font-family: Montserrat,sans-serif;}.evg-mail-form__grid {display: grid;grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;align-items: center;gap: 50px;}.evg-mail-form__image {max-width: 100%;border-radius: 7px;}.evg-mail-form__inputs {display: grid;grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;gap: 15px 10px;}.evg-mail-form__inputs #mce-responses {grid-column: 1/4;}.evg-mail-form__inputs input {width: 100%;box-sizing: border-box;font-size: 17px;padding: 10px 10px;border: 1px solid #bbb;outline: none;box-shadow: none;background-color: white;font-weight: 400;font-family: Montserrat,sans-ser